5:
How are you feeling? Are you used
to this place yet?
8:
I'm getting there... My fur still feels
weird...
12:
This place is amazing though! An
entire town on a big metal ship?
19:
So this is the power of the burny
gloop! Plus all that elemental gem
and alchemy stuff! They've got the
works here, huh?
21:
It's like a nonstop ride of inspiration!
Makes me want to jump back home
and start fixing up our world already.
26:
I feel the same. Everyone here is so
energetic and cheerful...
33:
Maybe my mom would've been
happy in a world like this.
47: Claw, Helga! Can you hold it?
52:
Haha, in this situation there is no
"can," only "must."
60:
Relax, we've got you. Hold onto us,
okay?
69: Are you hurt? No? Thank goodness...
70:
How many times have I told you not
to stand so close to the edge? The
ocean is dangerous!
72:
Thank you so much for saving my
boy! How can I ever repay you?
78:
You don't need to pay us anything!
We're just happy he's all right.
83:
You're very welcome. Make sure you
listen to your mom from now on,
okay?
97: Do you have some time after this?
101:
Is this... the hidden village of the
lionfolk?
104:
I had no idea there was a
settlement here...
108:
We were apparently pretty
self-sufficient, so we rarely traded
with other villages...
115:
As far back as I can remember, it
was only me and my mom.
Everyone else was already...
126:
But this tiny place was my mom's
entire world.
129:
My mom... never knew what the
outside world was like.
135:
...Should we give you a moment
alone?
139:
It's okay. I'm sorry for making you
come here with me.
142:
...If you don't mind, there's one more
place I want to visit.
145:
We'll stay with you for as long as you
want.
151:
...Hi, Mom. I get the feeling you might
be mad at me for trying, but...
153:
I promise I'll make this world one
where lionfolk people can
belong—one where you could've
been happy in.
160: Are you ready? I don't mind waiting.
163:
I'm ready. I can't be standing around
when there's so much to do.
166:
After everything's sorted, I'll come
again and tell her about all the
things I've done.
169: Is that so? Well, it's your choice.
171:
I don't know whether your efforts will
pay off, but—
176:
They will. I'll keep trying no matter
how many times it takes.
180:
I'm sorry. I don't know you
whatsoever, but this probably isn't
the life you wanted for him.
182:
You have nothing to worry about,
though. He's a strong one.
